The article discusses the importance of health care as a right for all Americans, especially during the ongoing pandemic. The author highlights the special enrollment period on HealthCare.gov, which has allowed over 200,000 Americans to sign up for health insurance. The article encourages those who still need coverage to take advantage of this opportunity before May 15. The author also emphasizes the need to lower health costs and mentions the passing of the American Rescue Plan by the House of Representatives. This plan aims to reduce premiums, expand access to care, increase federal subsidies, and incentivize states to extend coverage. The article concludes by stating that the American Rescue Plan is crucial for combating the pandemic and building a better future for Americans.